s believed to have been directed to Dōgo Onsen by Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto through an underwater channel. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Unzen|ja|雲仙市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Obama Onsen|ja|小浜町雲仙|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Unzen Onsen|ja|雲仙温泉|qq=draft}}) - A Kokusai-mizai-sha. Dedicated to the deity of Tsukushi Island (modern {{ill|Kyūshū|ja|九州|qq=draft}}), represented in the form of "Isshin Shimen" (a single body with four faces). The shrine is also known as "Shimen-gū." The name "Unzen" derives from the reading of 温泉 (onsen), but the shrine is pronounced as written: "Onsen Jinja." Over a dozen branch shrines of the same name exist within the {{ill|Shimabara Peninsula|ja|島原半島|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Shimabara)|ja|温泉神社 (島原市亀の甲町)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, {{ill|Shimabara|ja|島原市|qq=draft}}, Kamenokō-chō) * {{ill|Onsen Kumano Shrine|ja|温泉熊野神社|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Shimabara) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Kunimi)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市国見町多比良丁)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Kunimi-machi Tabirachō) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Azuma)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市吾妻町布江名)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Azuma-machi Fuenami) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Chijiwa)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市千々石町己)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Chijiwa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Ariake)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市有家町山川)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, {{ill|Minamishimabara|ja|南島原市|qq=draft}}, Ariake-machi Yamakawa) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Kazusa)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市加津佐町己)|qq=draft}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Minamishimabara, Kazusa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Yatsushiro)|ja|温泉神社 (八代市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Kumamoto Prefecture|ja|熊本県|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yatsushiro|ja|八代市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Hinagu Onsen|ja|日奈久温泉|qq=draft}}) - Enshrines Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|Onsen Temple|ja|温泉寺|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Onsen Origin Myth|ja|開湯伝説|1=Onsen Origin Myth|qq=draft}}
