to, and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Yu Shrine (Dōgo Onsen)|ja|湯神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yu Shrine (Dōgo Onsen)|qq=}} ({{ill|Ehime Prefecture|ja|愛媛県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Matsuyama|ja|松山市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsuyama|qq=}}, {{ill|Dōgo Onsen|ja|道後温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dōgo Onsen|qq=}}) - Shikinai-sha. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Higashidōgo Shrine|ja|東道後神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashidōgo Shrine|qq=}} (Ehime Prefecture, Matsuyama, {{ill|Higashidōgo Onsen|ja|東道後温泉郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashidōgo Onsen|qq=}}) - A subordinate shrine of {{ill|Hio Hachiman Shrine|ja|日尾八幡神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hio Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}. Enshrines Amenominakanushi-no-Kami, Amaterasu-Ōmikami, and Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Beppu)|ja|温泉神社 (別府市青山町)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Beppu)|qq=}} ({{ill|Ōita Prefecture|ja|大分県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōita Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Beppu|ja|別府市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu|qq=}}, {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu Onsen|qq=}}) - Founded during the Taishō period. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto, and others. Currently merged into {{ill|Hachiman Asami Shrine|ja|八幡朝見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Asami Shrine|qq=}}. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Beppu Tetsuwana)|ja|温泉神社 (別府市鉄輪)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Beppu Tetsuwana)|qq=}} (Ōita Prefecture, Beppu, {{ill|Tetsuwana Onsen|ja|鉄輪温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tetsuwana Onsen|qq=}}) * {{ill|Hinokuma Hime Shrine|ja|火男火売神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinokuma Hime Shrine|qq=}} (Ōita Prefecture, Beppu, Tetsuwana Onsen) - Shikinai-sha. Enshrines Hinokagutsuchi-no-Mikoto and Hiyakehayahime-no-Mikoto. It is said that {{ill|Ippen|ja|一遍|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ippen|qq=}} Shōnin was inspired by this shrine, called Tsurumi Gongen, to create a stone steam bath (mushi-yu). "Hayami no Yu," a hot spring flowing from the base of the sacred Tsurumidake mountain, is believed to have been directed to Dōgo Onsen by Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto through an underwater channel. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen)|qq=}} ({{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Unzen|ja|雲仙市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unzen|qq=}}, {{ill|Obama Onsen|ja|小浜町雲仙|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Obama Onsen|qq=}}, {{ill|Unzen Onsen|ja|雲仙温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unzen Onsen|qq=}}) - A Kokusai-mizai-sha. Dedicated to the deity of Tsukushi Island (modern {{ill|Kyūshū|ja|九州|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyūshū|qq=}}), represented in the form of "Isshin Shimen" (a single body with four faces). The shrine is also known as "Shimen-gū." The name "Unzen" derives from the reading of 温泉 (onsen), but the shrine is pronounced as written: "Onsen Jinja." Over a dozen branch shrines of the same name exist within the {{ill|Shimabara Peninsula|ja|島原半島|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimabara Peninsula|qq=}}. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Shimabara)|ja|温泉神社 (島原市亀の甲町)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Shimabara)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, {{ill|Shimabara|ja|島原市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimabara|qq=}}, Kamenokō-chō) * {{ill|Onsen Kumano Shrine|ja|温泉熊野神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Kumano Shrine|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Shimabara) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Kunimi)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市国見町多比良丁)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Kunimi)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Kunimi-machi Tabirachō) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Azuma)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市吾妻町布江名)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Azuma)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Azuma-machi Fuenami) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Chijiwa)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市千々石町己)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Chijiwa)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Chijiwa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Ariake)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市有家町山川)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Ariake)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, {{ill|Minamishimabara|ja|南島原市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamishimabara|qq=}}, Ariake-machi Yamakawa) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Kazusa)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市加津佐町己)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Kazusa)|qq=}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Minamishimabara, Kazusa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Yatsushiro)|ja|温泉神社 (八代市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Yatsushiro)|qq=}} ({{ill|Kumamoto Prefecture|ja|熊本県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumamoto Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Yatsushiro|ja|八代市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yatsushiro|qq=}}, {{ill|Hinagu Onsen|ja|日奈久温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinagu Onsen|qq=}}) - Enshrines Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|Onsen Temple|ja|温泉寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Temple|qq=}} * {{ill|Onsen Origin Myth|ja|開湯伝説|1=Onsen Origin Myth|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Origin Myth|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Origin Myth|qq=}}
