en|Iwaki Yumoto Onsen]]) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Kami|ja|事代主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}}, and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Ōtawara)|ja|温泉神社 (大田原市中野内)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Ōtawara)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi Prefecture]], [[:en:Ōtawara|Ōtawara]], {{ill|Kurobane Onsen|ja|黒羽温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurobane Onsen|qq=}}) - Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto, and others. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Nasushiobara)|ja|温泉神社 (那須塩原市湯本塩原)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Nasushiobara)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Tochigi Prefecture, [[:en:Nasushiobara|Nasushiobara]], {{ill|Shiobara Onsen|ja|塩原温泉郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiobara Onsen|qq=}}) - Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Nasu Onsen Shrine|ja|那須温泉神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nasu Onsen Shrine|qq=}} (Tochigi Prefecture, [[:en:Nasu District, Tochigi|Nasu District]], [[:en:Nasu, Tochigi|Nasu]], {{ill|Nasu Onsen|ja|那須温泉郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nasu Onsen|qq=}}) - Shikinaisha. Famous for the [[:en:Sessho-seki|Sessho-seki]]. The "Nasu Yumoto Daijingū" mentioned in the [[:en:The Tale of the Heike|Heike Monogatari]] is said to refer to this shrine. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Nikkō)|ja|温泉神社 (日光市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Nikkō)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Tochigi Prefecture, [[:en:Nikkō|Nikkō]], [[:en:Kinugawa Onsen|Kinugawa Onsen]]) * {{ill|Yumae Shrine|ja|湯前神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumae Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]], [[:en:Atami|Atami]], [[:en:Atami Onsen|Atami Onsen]]) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Izuyama Shrine|ja|射山神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izuyama Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], [[:en:Tsu, Mie|Tsu]], {{ill|Sakakibara Onsen|ja|榊原温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakakibara Onsen|qq=}}) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Yusen Shrine (Kobe)|ja|湯泉神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yusen Shrine (Kobe)|qq=}} ([[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]], [[:en:Kobe|Kobe]], [[:en:北區|Kita-ku (Kobe)]], [[:en:Arima Onsen|Arima Onsen]]) - Shikinaisha. Sometimes referred to as "Onsen Shrine." Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto, and Kumano-Kusumi-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Shisho Shrine (Toyooka)|ja|四所神社 (豊岡市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shisho Shrine (Toyooka)|qq=}} (Hyōgo Prefecture, [[:en:Toyooka, Hyōgo|Toyooka]], {{ill|Kinosaki Onsen|ja|城崎温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinosaki Onsen|qq=}}) - Enshrines Yuyama-no-Kami (湯山主神) and others. It is said that Dōchi, who visited this shrine, was divinely inspired to open the public bath "Mandarayu." * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Shirahama)|ja|温泉神社 (白浜町)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Shirahama)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Wakayama Prefecture|Wakayama Prefecture]], [[:en:Nishimuro District, Wakayama|Nishimuro District]], [[:en:Shirahama, Wakayama|Shirahama]], [[:en:Nanki-Shirahama Onsen|Nanki Shirahama Onsen]]) * {{ill|Yumoto Shrine|ja|湯本神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumoto Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Okayama Prefecture|Okayama Prefecture]], [[:en:Maniwa|Maniwa]], {{ill|Yubara Onsen|ja|湯原温泉|1=Yubara Onsen|2=ja|3=湯原温泉|4=ceb|5=Yubara hotspring|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yubara Onsen|13=User:Immanuelle/Yubara Onsen|qq=}}) - The location was formerly called Yubara, but upon Maniwa City's establishment, it was renamed Yubara Onsen. * {{ill|Miyu Shrine|ja|御湯神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyu Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Tottori Prefecture|Tottori Prefecture]], [[:en:Iwami District, Tottori|Iwami District]], [[:en:Iwami, Tottori|Iwami]], {{ill|Iwai Onsen|ja|岩井温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwai Onsen|qq=}}) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, Yakami-hime-no-Mikoto, Miino-Kami, and Sarutahiko-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Tamatsukuri Shrine|ja|玉作湯神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamatsukuri Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Shimane Prefecture|Shimane Prefecture]], [[:en:Matsue|Matsue]], [[:en:Tamatsukuri Onsen|Tamatsukuri Onsen]]) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Kushiakarutama-no-Kami, Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Yu Shrine|lt=Yu Shrine|lt=Yu Shrine (Dōgo Onsen)|ja|湯神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yu Shrine (Dōgo Onsen)|qq=}} ([[:en:Ehime Prefecture|Ehime Prefecture]], [[:en:Matsuyama|Matsuyama]], [[:en:Dōgo Onsen|Dōgo Onsen]]) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Higashidōgo Shrine|ja|東道後神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashidōgo Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 日尾八幡神社}} (Ehime Prefecture, Matsuyama, {{ill|Higashidōgo Onsen|ja|東道後温泉郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashidōgo Onsen|qq=}}) - A subordinate shrine of {{ill|Hio Hachiman Shrine|ja|日尾八幡神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hio Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}. Enshrines Amenominakanushi-no-Kami, Amaterasu-Ōmikami, and Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Beppu)|ja|温泉神社 (別府市青山町)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Beppu)|qq=}} ([[:en:Ōita Prefecture|Ōita Prefecture]], [[:en:Beppu|Beppu]], [[:en:Beppu Onsen|Beppu Onsen]]) - Founded during the Taishō period. Enshrines Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto, Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto, and others. Currently merged into {{ill|Hachiman Asami Shrine|ja|八幡朝見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Asami Shrine|qq=}}. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Beppu Tetsuwana)|ja|温泉神社 (別府市鉄輪)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Beppu Tetsuwana)|qq=}} (Ōita Prefecture, Beppu, {{ill|Tetsuwana Onsen|ja|鉄輪温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tetsuwana Onsen|qq=}}) * {{ill|Hinokuma Hime Shrine|ja|火男火売神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinokuma Hime Shrine|qq=}} (Ōita Prefecture, Beppu, Tetsuwana Onsen) - Shikinaisha. Enshrines Hinokagutsuchi-no-Mikoto and Hiyakehayahime-no-Mikoto. It is said that [[:en:Ippen|Ippen]] Shōnin was inspired by this shrine, called Tsurumi Gongen, to create a stone steam bath (mushi-yu). "Hayami no Yu," a hot spring flowing from the base of the sacred Tsurumidake mountain, is believed to have been directed to Dōgo Onsen by Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto through an underwater channel. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen)|qq=}} ([[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]], [[:en:Unzen, Nagasaki|Unzen]], {{ill|Obama Onsen|ja|小浜町雲仙|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Obama Onsen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, [[:en:Unzen Onsen|Unzen Onsen]]) - A Kokusai-mizai-sha. Dedicated to the deity of Tsukushi Island (modern [[:en:Kyushu|Kyūshū]]), represented in the form of "Isshin Shimen" (a single body with four faces). The shrine is also known as "Shimen-gū." The name "Unzen" derives from the reading of 温泉 (onsen), but the shrine is pronounced as written: "Onsen Jinja." Over a dozen branch shrines of the same name exist within the [[:en:Shimabara Peninsula|Shimabara Peninsula]]. * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Shimabara)|ja|温泉神社 (島原市亀の甲町)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Shimabara)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, [[:en:Shimabara, Nagasaki|Shimabara]], Kamenokō-chō) * {{ill|Onsen Kumano Shrine|ja|温泉熊野神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Kumano Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Shimabara) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Kunimi)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市国見町多比良丁)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Kunimi)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Kunimi-machi Tabirachō) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Azuma)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市吾妻町布江名)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Azuma)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Azuma-machi Fuenami) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Unzen Chijiwa)|ja|温泉神社 (雲仙市千々石町己)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Unzen Chijiwa)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Unzen, Chijiwa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Ariake)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市有家町山川)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Ariake)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, [[:en:Minamishimabara|Minamishimabara]], Ariake-machi Yamakawa) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Kazusa)|ja|温泉神社 (南島原市加津佐町己)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Minamishimabara Kazusa)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Nagasaki Prefecture, Minamishimabara, Kazusa-machi Mi) * {{ill|Onsen Shrine (Yatsushiro)|ja|温泉神社 (八代市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine (Yatsushiro)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Kumamoto Prefecture|Kumamoto Prefecture]], [[:en:Yatsushiro|Yatsushiro]], {{ill|Hinagu Onsen|ja|日奈久温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinagu Onsen|qq=}}) - Enshrines Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|Onsen Temple|ja|温泉寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Temple|qq=}} * {{ill|Onsen Origin Myth|ja|開湯伝説|1=Onsen Origin Myth|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Origin Myth|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Origin Myth|qq=}}
